Yes one thing I want to try soon that I didn&#39;t mention in my last post 
was &#39;phased searching&#39; - the idea I mentioned previously whereby the 
search switches between normal searching (adding connections and nodes) 
and a &#39;genome trimming&#39; search phase. I&#39;d like to find out if this helps 
with high input/output spaces, I was thinking of using an OCR type 
domain since it&#39;s simple to implement, not CPU intensive and also a 
domain that has been successfuly solved with more traditional techniques 
such as back-propagation. Mattias&#39; DelphiNEAT also has a demo EXE that 
attempts this problem with a standard NEAT search (I assume anyway) and 
it sems to perform quite poorly :(

